# Ways of working

## Quality checks
You should have an agreed and documented quality checking process. 

Your process should:

- be appropriate for your service
- take into account different levels of changes. For example, typo, minor content update, policy change
- include how and when you conduct activities such as: 

  - 2i and peer reviews
  - fact checking
  - policy sign-off
  - communications

You should conduct your final quality checks on a preview of the content as it would appear once published. 


